(
<figureCitation id="4E9568F9E85AA57F5D4A5266FE7DA635" box="[339,403,1830,1856]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,1106,1811]" captionTargetId="figure-423@11.[151,1436,1101,1811]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 4. Host plant, two variations of Taquara micrantha. Taquara micrantha with pubescence on the abaxial surface as a host plant for Nhambikuara mima and Paryphthimoides brixius: 1a) leaves; 1b) close-up view of the node and abaxial part showing pubescence; 1c) inflorescence materials; 1d) host plant in situ. Taquara micrantha lacking pubescence for Splendeuptychia furina: 2a) leaves and inflorescence in situ; 2b) close-up view of nodes; 2c) close-up view of abaxial surface showing lack of pubescence; 2d) host plant in situ." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6420370" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6420370/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Fig 4</figureCitation>
: 2a–d). 
<taxonomicName id="11AE0FFFE85AA57F5DF55267FB9AA635" authority="(Kunth) I. L. C. Oliveira &amp; R. P. Oliveira" authorityName="I. L. C. Oliveira &amp; R. P. Oliveira" baseAuthorityName="Kunth" box="[492,1140,1830,1857]" class="Arachnida" family="Cryptogeobiidae" genus="Taquara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="micrantha">
